// C3: Physical sensing components
instance LiDARPointCloudSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "LiDAR sensor capturing raw point cloud data for spatial environment representation"
    DTDFVocab:producedData LiDARPointCloudDataTransmitted
]

instance VehicleStateSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Vehicle telemetry sensor providing real-time state data (speed, position, orientation)"
    DTDFVocab:producedData VehicleStateDataTransmitted
]

instance MotorActuationSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Motor actuation sensor providing feedback on motor torque and operational state"
    DTDFVocab:producedData MotorActuationDataTransmitted
]

instance SteeringServoSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Steering servo sensor providing feedback on steering angles and servo state"
    DTDFVocab:producedData SteeringServoDataTransmitted
]

instance DataPreProcessingSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Data preprocessing component handling initial filtering, noise reduction, and alignment of sensor streams"
    DTDFVocab:producedData PreProcessedSensorDataTransmitted
]

// C4: Physical-to-virtual interaction
instance LiDARPointCloudDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    base:desc "Raw LiDAR point cloud data transmitted via UDP/Wi-Fi for real-time processing"
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom LiDARPointCloudSensor
]

instance VehicleStateDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    base:desc "Real-time vehicle telemetry data (speed, position, orientation) transmitted via UDP/Wi-Fi"
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom VehicleStateSensor
]

instance MotorActuationDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    base:desc "Motor actuation commands and feedback transmitted via UDP/Wi-Fi for control synchronization"
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom MotorActuationSensor
]

instance SteeringServoDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    base:desc "Steering servo commands and feedback transmitted via UDP/Wi-Fi for control synchronization"
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom SteeringServoSensor
]

instance PreProcessedSensorDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    base:desc "Filtered and aligned sensor data streams after preprocessing"
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom DataPreProcessingSensor
]

instance PointCloudClusteringAndTrackingModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Software component converting raw 2D point cloud data into structured object tracks and spatial clusters"
    DTDFVocab:inputTo PointCloudClusteringAndTrackingEnabler
]

instance VehicleStateModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Digital representation of vehicle state for real-time monitoring and control"
    DTDFVocab:inputTo VehicleStateProcessingEnabler
]

instance LiDARPointCloudData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Processed LiDAR point cloud data ready for visualization and analysis"
    DTDFVocab:fromData LiDARPointCloudDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo PointCloudClusteringAndTrackingEnabler
]

instance VehicleStateData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Processed vehicle state data (speed, position, orientation) for real-time monitoring"
    DTDFVocab:fromData VehicleStateDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo VehicleStateProcessingEnabler
]

instance MotorActuationData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Processed motor actuation data for control feedback and optimization"
    DTDFVocab:fromData MotorActuationDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo ActuationControlEnabler
]

instance SteeringServoData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Processed steering servo data for control feedback and optimization"
    DTDFVocab:fromData SteeringServoDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo ActuationControlEnabler
]

instance PreProcessedSensorData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Filtered and aligned sensor data streams for unified processing"
    DTDFVocab:fromData PreProcessedSensorDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo DataTranslationEnabler
]

instance ACCRelevantDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    base:desc "Adaptive Cruise Control (ACC) data including projected driving paths and object tracks"
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom PointCloudClusteringAndTrackingModel
]

instance ACCRelevantData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Processed ACC data including projected driving paths and object tracks for autonomous control"
    DTDFVocab:fromData ACCRelevantDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo AdaptiveCruiseControlEnabler
]

instance ThreeDVisualizationData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Processed data rendered in 3D visualization for real-time monitoring"
    DTDFVocab:fromData LiDARPointCloudData
    DTDFVocab:inputTo VisualizationEnabler
]

instance ThreeDVisualizationData2 : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Processed data rendered in 3D visualization for real-time monitoring"
    DTDFVocab:fromData VehicleStateData
    DTDFVocab:inputTo VisualizationEnabler
]

instance ThreeDVisualizationData3 : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Processed data rendered in 3D visualization for real-time monitoring"
    DTDFVocab:fromData ACCRelevantData
    DTDFVocab:inputTo VisualizationEnabler
]

// C11: Enablers
instance PointCloudClusteringAndTrackingEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "ROS2-based software component for point cloud clustering and tracking"
    DTDFVocab:enables PointCloudClusteringAndTrackingService
]

instance VehicleStateProcessingEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "ROS2-based software component for processing vehicle state data"
    DTDFVocab:enables VehicleStateMonitoringService
]

instance ActuationControlEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "ROS2-based software component for motor and servo actuation control"
    DTDFVocab:enables ActuationControlService
]

instance DataTranslationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "ISO 23247-compliant component ensuring serialization, message type alignment, and unit conversions"
    DTDFVocab:enables DataTranslationService
]

instance AdaptiveCruiseControlEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Software component handling ACC data processing and control decisions"
    DTDFVocab:enables AdaptiveCruiseControlService
]

instance VisualizationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "3D visualization engine (e.g., Unity, Unreal Engine) for real-time monitoring"
    DTDFVocab:enables ThreeDVisualizationService
]

instance ROS2NetworkEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "ROS2 network for intra-entity communication within Digital Twin Entity"
    DTDFVocab:enables ROS2CommunicationService
]

instance UDPWiFiNetworkEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Wi-Fi network using UDP protocol for physical-to-digital data transmission"
    DTDFVocab:enables PhysicalToDigitalDataTransmissionService
]

// C6: Services
instance PointCloudClusteringAndTrackingService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service converting raw point cloud data into structured object tracks and spatial clusters"
    DTDFVocab:provides PointCloudClusteringInsight
]

instance VehicleStateMonitoringService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service providing real-time vehicle state monitoring and telemetry"
    DTDFVocab:provides VehicleStateInsight
]

instance ActuationControlService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service managing motor and servo actuation commands and feedback"
    DTDFVocab:provides ActuationControlAction
]

instance DataTranslationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service ensuring data serialization, message type alignment, and unit conversions"
    DTDFVocab:provides DataTranslationInsight
]

instance AdaptiveCruiseControlService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service handling ACC data processing and autonomous control decisions"
    DTDFVocab:provides AdaptiveCruiseControlAction
]

instance ThreeDVisualizationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service rendering processed data in 3D visualization for real-time monitoring"
    DTDFVocab:provides ThreeDVisualizationInsight
]

instance ROS2CommunicationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service enabling modular integration of data streams via ROS2 topic-based communication"
    DTDFVocab:provides ROS2CommunicationInsight
]

instance PhysicalToDigitalDataTransmissionService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service facilitating low-latency transmission of processed data via UDP/Wi-Fi"
    DTDFVocab:provides PhysicalToDigitalDataTransmissionInsight
]

// C17: Insights/Actions
instance PointCloudClusteringInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Structured object tracks and spatial clusters derived from raw LiDAR point cloud data"
]

instance VehicleStateInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Real-time vehicle state including speed, position, and orientation for monitoring"
]

instance ActuationControlAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Automatic generation and execution of motor and servo actuation commands"
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance DataTranslationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Ensured data consistency through serialization, message type alignment, and unit conversions"
]

instance AdaptiveCruiseControlAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Automatic generation of ACC control decisions based on projected driving paths and object tracks"
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance ThreeDVisualizationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Real-time 3D visualization combining LiDAR-derived object tracks, vehicle state, and ACC paths"
]

instance ROS2CommunicationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Modular integration of data streams via ROS2 topic-based communication"
]

instance PhysicalToDigitalDataTransmissionInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Low-latency transmission of processed data from physical to digital domain via UDP/Wi-Fi"
]

// C1: Functional Entities (Physical Twin Entity)
instance PhysicalTwinEntity : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Hosts resource-specific and general automotive functionality including point cloud clustering, tracking, and sensor data processing"
    base:isContainedIn DecentralizedDigitalTwinSystemEnvironment
]

// C1: Functional Entities (Digital Twin Entity)
instance DigitalTwinEntity : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Manages data collection, processing, and control mechanisms for the digital twin system"
    base:isContainedIn DecentralizedDigitalTwinSystemEnvironment
]

// C1: Functional Entities (User Entity)
instance UserEntity : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Provides user-facing components including 3D visualization and control panel"
    base:isContainedIn DecentralizedDigitalTwinSystemEnvironment
]

// C1: Subcomponents (User Interface FE)
instance ThreeDVisualizationSubcomponent : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Subcomponent responsible for rendering 3D visualizations of processed data"
    base:isContainedIn UserEntity
]

instance ControlPanelSubcomponent : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Subcomponent providing control interfaces for user interaction"
    base:isContainedIn UserEntity
]

// C1: Environment
instance DecentralizedDigitalTwinSystemEnvironment : DTDFVocab:Environment [
    base:desc "Decentralized architecture where each functional entity is deployed as an independent ROS2 package on distinct hardware components"
    base:contains PhysicalTwinEntity, DigitalTwinEntity, UserEntity
]

instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "
The **virtual-to-physical interaction** in this Digital Twin System (DTS) is governed by the following control flows and mechanisms:

1. **Command Types**:
   - **Actuation Commands**: Generated by the *Actuation FE* to control physical components (e.g., motor torque adjustments, steering servo angles).
   - **ACC Control Signals**: Issued by the *Controlling FE* (ACC module) to regulate vehicle speed and distance via throttle/brake interventions.
   - **User-Triggered Commands**: Sent from the *User Interface FE* (e.g., control panel inputs) to override or adjust system parameters.

2. **Control Message Formats**:
   - Standardized via the *Data Translation* component, which ensures **message type alignment** and **unit conversions** (e.g., converting digital control signals to physical actuation units).
   - Compatible with **ROS2 message formats** for intra-entity communication and **UDP packets** for Wi-Fi-based transmission to physical actuators.

3. **Validation and Authentication Mechanisms**:
   - **Not explicitly detailed in the document**, but implied via the *Data Translation* component’s role in ensuring data integrity and consistency across the system.
   - **Legacy System Integration**: The *Legacy Data Translation* component suggests compatibility checks for older systems, though specifics are absent.

4. **Feedback Systems**:
   - **Closed-Loop Control**: Actuation commands (e.g., motor/servo outputs) are monitored via sensor feedback (e.g., LiDAR, vehicle state) to adjust control signals dynamically.
   - **Real-Time Visualization Feedback**: The *3D Visualization* (Fig. 3a) provides operators with a live view of command effects (e.g., vehicle trajectory, object avoidance), enabling manual overrides if needed.

5. **Conflict Resolution**:
   - **Priority-Based Arbitration**: Implied by the *Controlling FE* (ACC) and *Actuation FE* hierarchy, where safety-critical commands (e.g., collision avoidance) may preempt user inputs.
   - **Data Translation Mediation**: Resolves inconsistencies in message formats or units before execution.

6. **Command Execution Confirmation**:
   - **Acknowledgment via Sensor Feedback**: Physical actuators (e.g., motors, servos) provide state updates (e.g., position, torque) back to the Digital Twin, confirming command execution.
   - **Visual Confirmation**: The *Presentation FE* updates the 3D visualization to reflect the physical system’s response to commands (e.g., vehicle movement in Fig. 3b).
"
]

instance twinning_time_scale : DTDFVocab:TimeScale [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin System (DTS) enforces a **100 ms time synchronization accuracy** between physical and digital components to enable computation offloading and coordination, adhering to hardware limitations. This temporal granularity is critical for safety-critical vehicular applications, where stricter clock synchronization (e.g., sub-100 ms) is mandated by many standards. The system does not explicitly specify varying time scales for different services or latency requirements beyond this synchronization constraint, but the 100 ms threshold implies real-time operational constraints for data exchange and actuation. No further details on temporal granularity for specific services (e.g., sensor fusion, visualization) are provided in the document."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The DTS orchestrates coordination through a **ROS2-based microservices architecture**, where each FE is implemented as a modular ROS2 package containing one or more nodes. Key orchestration mechanisms include:
  - **Entity-based mapping**: Software components are mapped to functional entities (*Physical Twin*, *Digital Twin*, *User*) as per ISO 23247, but with **custom deviations** (e.g., *Physical Twin Entity* hosting general automotive functions).
  - **Component integration**: ROS2 provides inter-node communication via topics/services, enabling loose coupling between entities. The *User Entity* consolidates user-facing components (*3D Visualization*, *Control Panel*), while the *Digital Twin Entity* manages data/control logic, and the *Physical Twin Entity* handles pre-processing, actuation, and device communication.
  - **Resource management**: Hardware-specific deployment of entities ensures resource isolation (e.g., compute, sensors, actuators), but may introduce **ownership conflicts** due to deviations from ISO 23247. The system does not specify dynamic resource allocation or load balancing mechanisms."
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "
The **technical network infrastructure** for this Digital Twin System (DTS) is defined by the following specifications:

1. **Communication Protocols**:
   - **Intra-Entity (Software Components)**: **ROS2 (Robot Operating System 2)** network for high-speed, modular communication between software components (e.g., *Point Cloud Clustering & Tracking* → *Data Translation* → *Controlling FE*).
   - **Inter-Entity (Physical-Digital)**: **Wi-Fi with UDP** at the transport layer for transmitting sensor/actuation data between the Physical Twin (vehicle) and Digital Twin entities.

2. **Network Topology and Architecture**:
   - **Hierarchical Model**:
     - **Physical Twin Entity**: Sources raw data (LiDAR, motor/servo states, vehicle telemetry).
     - **Digital Twin Entity**: Hosts processing components (*Data Pre-Processing FE*, *Controlling FE*, *Presentation FE*) and visualization interfaces.
     - **User Entity**: Interfaces via *User Interface FE* (control panel, 3D cockpit).
   - **Data Flow Paths**: Illustrated in Fig. 2, showing sensor data propagation from Physical Twin → Digital Twin → User Entity.

3. **Bandwidth and Latency Requirements**:
   - **Real-Time Constraints**: Critical for LiDAR point cloud processing and ACC control, though exact bandwidth/latency thresholds are not specified.
   - **UDP Optimization**: Prioritizes low-latency transmission over reliability for time-sensitive data (e.g., collision avoidance commands).

4. **Reliability and Redundancy Mechanisms**:
   - **Not explicitly detailed**, but implied via:
     - **Data Translation**: Ensures data consistency across components.
     - **ROS2 Topic-Based Redundancy**: Multiple subscribers can receive the same data stream (e.g., LiDAR tracks for visualization and control).
   - **Legacy System Compatibility**: The *Legacy Data Translation* component suggests support for fallback mechanisms if modern protocols fail.

5. **Security Protocols**:
   - **Not in Document**: No mention of encryption, authentication, or access control measures for network communication.
"
]

instance dt_hosting_deployment : DTDFVocab:Deployment [
    base:desc "
The **deployment infrastructure** for this Digital Twin System (DTS) is characterized by the following technical and operational aspects:

1. **Hosting Platforms**:
   - **Edge Deployment**: Implied by the **on-board processing** of sensor data (e.g., LiDAR clustering, vehicle state analysis) within the Digital Twin Entity, minimizing cloud dependency.
   - **On-Premise Components**: Physical Twin Entity (vehicle) hosts sensors and actuators, while the Digital Twin Entity likely runs on **embedded systems** or **local servers** for real-time processing.

2. **Computational and Storage Requirements**:
   - **Computational**:
     - **Point Cloud Processing**: Requires high-performance computing for real-time clustering and tracking of LiDAR data.
     - **ACC Control Logic**: Demands low-latency processing for adaptive cruise control decisions.
     - **ROS2 Network**: Supports distributed computing across multiple nodes (e.g., *Data Pre-Processing FE*, *Controlling FE*).
   - **Storage**:
     - **Data Collecting FE**: Aggregates raw and processed data for reporting and analysis.
     - **Reporting FE**: Generates structured reports, implying storage for historical data (specific storage type not detailed).

3. **Scalability Mechanisms**:
   - **Modular ROS2 Architecture**: Enables horizontal scaling by adding nodes (e.g., additional LiDAR processors or control modules) without redesigning the core system.
   - **Component-Based Design**: Each FE (*Data Pre-Processing FE*, *Controlling FE*, etc.) can be scaled independently based on workload (e.g., higher-resolution LiDAR requires more clustering nodes).

4. **Deployment Models Supported**:
   - **Hybrid Edge-Cloud**: While primarily edge-deployed (on-board vehicle processing), the system may leverage cloud resources for non-real-time tasks (e.g., long-term data storage or analytics).
   - **Legacy Integration**: Supports integration with older systems via the *Legacy Data Translation* component, suggesting backward compatibility.

5. **Availability and Reliability Assurance**:
   - **Real-Time Processing**: Critical for safety applications (e.g., ACC), though specific uptime guarantees are not provided.
   - **Redundancy via ROS2**: Multiple nodes can subscribe to the same data streams, improving fault tolerance.
   - **Not in Document**: No explicit mention of failover mechanisms, backup systems, or disaster recovery protocols.
"
]

instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system adheres to the **ISO 23247 standard for Digital Twin frameworks in manufacturing**, specifically **Part 2: Reference Architecture**, which defines an **entity-based architecture** comprising four core entities: **Observable Manufacturing Element (OME)**, **Data Collection and Device Control Entity**, **Digital Twin Entity**, and **User Entity**. The standard ensures **interoperability** through modular **Functional Entities (FEs)** and does not mandate specific technologies (e.g., **OPC UA** is cited as a permissible choice for implementation). **Compliance frameworks** are not explicitly detailed beyond ISO 23247, though the standard’s structure aligns with broader **manufacturing digitalization standards** (e.g., Industry 4.0 principles). **Certification requirements** or **formal validation processes** are not mentioned, and **specifications for data exchange** (beyond the entity-based interaction model) are limited to the standard’s high-level framework. The absence of explicit **interoperability standards** (e.g., OPC UA, MTConnect, or STEP) beyond the reference architecture suggests flexibility in adoption."
]

instance security_and_safety_considerations : DTDFVocab:SecuritySafety [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system, particularly in the context of **ISO 26262-1:2018 (Road vehicles – Functional safety)** and **ISO 15622:2018 (Intelligent Transport Systems – Adaptive Cruise Control Systems)**, incorporates **functional safety measures** aligned with **Automotive Safety Integrity Level (ASIL)** requirements. This includes:
  - **Cybersecurity protocols**: Integration with **V2X (Vehicle-to-Everything) security frameworks** as outlined in **3GPP TS 22.185 v15.0.0**, which mandates **authentication, encryption (e.g., TLS 1.2+), and secure communication channels** for real-time data exchange between vehicles and infrastructure.
  - **Access control mechanisms**: Role-based access control (RBAC) for system components, ensuring **least-privilege principles** in safety-critical subsystems (e.g., adaptive cruise control).
  - **Authentication systems**: **Digital certificates and cryptographic key management** (e.g., ECDSA) for validating entity identities in V2X communications, as specified in **3GPP TS 22.185**.
  - **Threat mitigation strategies**: **Intrusion detection systems (IDS)** and **anomaly-based monitoring** for detecting unauthorized access or data tampering in real-time.
  - **Fail-safe mechanisms**: **Redundant system architectures** with **watchdog timers** and **fail-operational designs** (e.g., ISO 26262-compliant hardware/software redundancy) to ensure graceful degradation in case of faults.
  - **Risk assessment approaches**: **Hazard Analysis and Risk Assessment (HARA)** methodology (ISO 26262) to identify safety risks, with **ASIL decomposition** to allocate safety requirements to system components.
  - **Safety-critical system considerations**: **Model-driven development (MDD)** techniques (as referenced in **Dalibor et al., 2020**) for designing **safety-critical Digital Twin cockpits**, ensuring traceability from requirements to implementation via **SysML/UML models** and **formal verification** of safety properties.
  - **Compliance with standards**: Adherence to **ISO 26262** for functional safety, including **safety lifecycle processes**, **safety validation**, and **safety case documentation** for regulatory approval (e.g., Type Approval)."
]